        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8322",
        "content": "On august nineteenth eighteen sixty one, a war tax of fifty cents on each hundred dollars of certain classes of property was levied for the special purpose of paying the principal and interest of the public debt, and of supporting the Government.",
